'''卡文迪什试验'''（'''Cavendish experiment'''，又稱'''卡文迪许扭秤实验'''），由[[亨利·卡文迪什|亨利·卡文迪什]]於1797年8月5日至1798年5月完成<ref>{{le|自閉群像|NeuroTribes}} p55</ref>。是第一个在实验室內完成的测量两个物体之间[[万有引力|万有引力]]的实验，并且第一个准确地求出了[[万有引力常数|万有引力常数]]和[[地球质量|地球质量]]<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=ZrloHemOmUEC&pg=PA355 Boys 1894] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ZrloHemOmUEC&pg=PA355 |date=20190711191637 }} p.355</ref><ref>Many sources state erroneously that this was the first measurement of G (or the Earth's density), such as {{Citation|last=Feynman|first=Richard P.|title=Lectures on Physics, Vol.1|year=1963|publisher=Addison-Wesley|pages=6–7|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=k6MQrphL-NIC&pg=PA28|id=ISBN 0201021161|format={{dead link|date=June 2008}} – <sup>[http://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?hl=en&lr=&q=author%3AFeynman+intitle%3ALectures+on+Physics%2C+Vol.1&as_publication=&as_ylo=&as_yhi=&btnG=Search Scholar search]</sup>}}.  There were previous measurements, chiefly Bouguer (1740) and Maskelyne (1774), but they were very inaccurate ([http://books.google.com/books?id=dg0RAAAAIAAJ Poynting 1894] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=dg0RAAAAIAAJ |date=20150324071536 }})([http://books.google.com/books?id=DgTALFa3sa4C&pg=PA385 Encyclopedia Britannica 1910] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=DgTALFa3sa4C&pg=PA385 |date=20190710183128 }}).</ref>。其他人则藉由他的实验结果求得了[[地球|地球]][[密度|密度]]。<ref>Clotfelter 1987, p.210</ref>

==歷史==
这个实验在1783年之前<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=EUoLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA336&sig=--1AlZ9rl_0AEL7h73LZvtK01S4 McCormmach & Jungnickel 1996] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=EUoLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA336&sig=--1AlZ9rl_0AEL7h73LZvtK01S4 |date=20140101152718 }}, p.336: A 1783 letter from Cavendish to Michell contains '...the earliest mention of weighing the world'. Not clear whether 'earliest mention' refers to Cavendish or Michell.</ref>由[[約翰·米歇爾|約翰·米歇爾]]设想出来<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA59 Cavendish 1798] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA59 |date=20190710151014 }}, p.59 Cavendish gives full credit to Michell for devising the experiment</ref>，他为此制作了一个[[扭秤|扭秤]]仪器。然而他并未完成这个实验，并于1793年[[去世|去世]]。他去世后，他的仪器传给{{tsl|en|Francis John Hyde Wollaston|弗朗西斯·約翰·海德·沃拉斯頓}}，之后又传给卡文迪什。卡文迪什复原了这个仪器并继续用它实现米歇爾原本的实验目标。

卡文迪什通过这个仪器进行了一系列的测量，之后于1798年在《[[自然科學會報|自然科學會報]]》上发表了自己的实验结果。

== 实验 ==
卡文迪什制造的实验装置是一台扭秤。用线捆绑的1.8m长的木棍两端各有一个直径{{convert|2|in|0|adj=on}}，重为{{convert|1.61|lb|adj=on}}的[[铅|铅]]制球。两个直径{{convert|12|in|adj=on}}，重为{{convert|348|lb|adj=on}}的大铅球分别放在小球附近大约{{convert|9|in}}远，各自用悬挂装置挂起<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA59 Cavendish 1798] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA59 |date=20190710151014 }}, p.59</ref> 。实验即测量大球和小球之间微弱的引力。
[[File:Cavendish_Experiment.png|thumb]]
[[File:CavendishSchematic111.jpg|thumb]]

两个大球放在水平木棒的两侧，使得它们施加于小球的力使木棒向同一个方向旋转。小球和木棒受力旋转后，吊起木棒的丝线就会旋转，直到丝线中产生的反向[[力矩|力矩]]与大小球之间引力的力矩平衡为止。测量木棒转过的角度可以知道丝线扭转后产生的力矩，进而可以得出大小铅球之间的引力大小。地球和铅球之间的引力可以經由测量铅球所受的重力直接得出，因此根据[[万有引力定律|万有引力定律]]可直接得到地球的质量，以及密度。

藉著卡文迪什的实验数据得到的地球密度为水的密度的{{val|5.448|0.033}}倍，而他本人在论文中的结论是{{val|5.480|0.038}}倍。1821年[[弗朗西斯·贝利|弗朗西斯·贝利]]找到了导致错误的一个计算问题。<ref name="Poynting 1894">[https://books.google.com/books?id=dg0RAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA45 Poynting 1894] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dg0RAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA45 |date=20190716050120 }}, p.45</ref><ref>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Cavendish, Henry |volume=5 |pages=580–581}}</ref>

测量了木棒转过的角度<math>\theta</math>之后，还需要知道丝线的扭转系数<math>\kappa</math>，才能求得丝线产生的力矩<math>\tau</math>：

:<math> \tau=-\kappa\theta </math>

为了得到丝线的扭转系数，卡文迪什测量了丝线和木棒在稳定之前，作[[简谐运动|简谐旋转]]时的自然周期。这一周期<math>T</math>大约为20分钟。再根据木棒的[[转动惯量|转动惯量]]<math>I</math>，即可求出扭转系数：

:<math>T=2\pi\sqrt{\frac{I}{\kappa}}</math><ref>{{cite book|author1=赵凯华|author2=罗蔚茵|editor=胡凯飞|title=新概念物理教程.力学|date=2004年7月|publisher=高等教育出版社|location=北京|isbn=978-7-04-015201-2|pages=249-250|edition=2版|language=zh-hans|chapter=第六章.第一节|quote=(6.5)(6.7)式}}</ref>

实际上，木棒很难完全静止，所以卡文迪什不得不在木棒轻微旋转时测量旋转角。<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA64 Cavendish 1798] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA64 |date=20190716225915 }}, p.64</ref>

而使扭秤旋转的力非常小，大约<math>1.74*10^{-7}</math>[[牛顿_(单位)|N]]<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=ZrloHemOmUEC&pg=PA357 Boys 1894] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZrloHemOmUEC&pg=PA357 |date=20190711091223 }} p.357</ref>，大约是小球质量的{{frac|50,000,000}}，卡文迪什的设备的灵敏度在当时是非常高的<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA60 Cavendish 1798] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA60 |date=20190719180255 }} p. 60</ref>。 为了防止空气流动和温度变化带来的测量误差，卡文迪什把整个装置放在他住宅内的一个小蓬里，用长{{convert|2|ft|m}}、宽{{convert|10|ft|m}}、高{{convert|10|ft|m}}的木盒子里。通过小蓬上的两个洞，卡文迪什用望远镜观察扭秤的运动。木棒的位置变化大约{{convert|0.16|in}}<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA99 Cavendish 1798] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA99 |date=20190715154428 }}, p. 99, Result table, (scale graduations = {{frac|20}} in ≈ 1.3 mm) The total deflection shown in most trials was twice this since he compared the deflection with large balls on opposite sides of the balance beam.</ref>。卡文迪什通过木棒末端的[[游标卡尺|游标卡尺]]对微小转动进行测量，精度超过百分之一英寸<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA63 Cavendish 1798] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA63 |date=20190711164605 }}, p.63</ref>。卡文迪什实验的测量精度在1895年才被[[查理士·凡而儂·波伊斯|查理士·凡而儂·波伊斯]]的实验超过。那时，卡文迪什的扭秤法成了测量[[万有引力常数|万有引力常数]]的主流方法，许多当代实验方法也从扭秤法衍生而来。这也是卡文迪什做的实验现在被称为“卡文迪什实验”的原因<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=EUoLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA341 McCormmach & Jungnickel 1996] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EUoLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA341 |date=20190714051026 }}, p.341</ref>。

==成就==
该实验是物理学史上的经典实验之一。这是科学家第一次测量并得到比较精确的万有引力常数，这样，对于天体以及地球质量的估计才成为可能。实验的难点在于完全去除环境的干扰，以及扭秤和光标的精度。卡文迪许在这方面做出了创造性的工作，其实验精度，在后续的近百年时间里，没有人能超过。在18世纪的工艺条件下，完成这样精度的实验是一个伟大的成就。

==与万有引力常数的关系==
在卡文迪什的年代，以[[万有引力常数|万有引力常数]]描述的[[牛顿万有引力定律|牛顿万有引力定律]]还未成为引力的标准描述方法。直到1873年才首次提到[[万有引力常数|万有引力常数]]G。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cornu |first1=A. |last2=Baille |first2=J. B. |date=1873 |url=http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3033b/f954.image |title=Détermination nouvelle de la constante de l'attraction et de la densité moyenne de la Terre |language=fr |trans_title=New Determination of the Constant of Attraction and the Average Density of Earth |journal=C. R. Acad. Sci. |location=Paris |volume=76 |issue= |pages=954–958 |doi= |access-date=2017-08-07 |archive-date=2020-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930005617/https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3033b/f954.image |dead-url=no }}</ref>

卡文迪什以地球的密度作为这一实验的最终结果，他将其称为“测量地球的重量”。后人将他的结果改写为现代的表达形式<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=ZrloHemOmUEC&pg=PA353 Boys 1894] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZrloHemOmUEC&pg=PA353 |date=20190714235230 }}, p.330 In this lecture before the Royal Society, Boys introduces ''G'' and argues for its acceptance</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=dg0RAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA4 Poynting 1894] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dg0RAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA4 |date=20190714142449 }}, p.4</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA1 MacKenzie 1900] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O58mAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA1 |date=20190711045714 }}, p.vi</ref>：
:<math>G = g\frac{R_\text{earth}^2}{M_\text{earth}} = \frac{3g}{4\pi R_\text{earth}\rho_\text{earth}}\,</math>
转换为[[国际单位制|国际单位制]]后，结果为<math>5.448g/cm^3</math>，得到<math>G=6.74\times 10^{-11} m^3\cdot kg^{-1}\cdot s^{-2} </math>，与2014年[[科学技术数据委员会|科学技术数据委员会]]推荐的[[万有引力常数|万有引力常数]]值相差小于1%。

因此，物理学史界认为卡文迪什并没有测出引力常数<ref>Clotfelter 1987</ref><ref name="McCormmach & Jungnickel 1996">[https://books.google.com/books?id=EUoLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA336 McCormmach & Jungnickel 1996] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EUoLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA336 |date=20190711235624 }}, p.337</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.public.iastate.edu/~lhodges/Michell.htm |title=Hodges 1999 |access-date=2017-08-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906134148/http://www.public.iastate.edu/~lhodges/Michell.htm |archive-date=2017-09-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>Lally 1999</ref>。然而物理学家有时会使用非国际单位制单位。例如[[高斯引力常数|高斯引力常数]]定义为一个定值，而卡文迪什实验则可视作对于[[天文单位|天文单位]]的测量。在卡文迪什的时代，物理学家对[[质量|质量]]和[[重量|重量]]使用相同的单位，采用[[重力加速度|g]]作为标准的重力加速度。当[[地球半径|地球半径]]已知时，地球的[[密度|密度]]也就表征了引力常数。因此地球的密度在当时是一个颇受关注的物理量。1774年进行的[[榭赫倫實驗|榭赫倫實驗]]就是一个尝试测量地球密度的实验。由此，物理学家一般不认为卡文迪什是首个测量出重力加速度的人。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Halliday|first=David|last2=Resnick|first2=Robert|title=Fundamentals of Physics|year=1993|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-471-14731-2|page=418|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-AjnmJHPiKMC&pg=PA418|postscript=<!--None-->|accessdate=2013-12-30}} 'The apparatus used in 1798 by Henry Cavendish to measure the gravitational constant'</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Feynman|first=Richard P.|title=Lectures on Physics, Vol.1|year=1963|publisher=Addison-Wesley|pages=6–7|url=http://www.feynmanlectures.caltech.edu/I_07.html#Ch7-S6|ISBN=0-201-02116-1|postscript=<!--None-->}} 'Cavendish claimed he was weighing the Earth, but what he was measuring was the coefficient ''G''...'</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Feynman|first=Richard P.|title=The Character of Physical Law|year=1967|publisher=MIT Press|pages=28|url=http://www.feynmanlectures.caltech.edu/I_07.html#Ch7-S6|ISBN=0-262-56003-8|postscript=<!--None-->}} 'Cavendish was able to measure the force, the two masses, and the distance, and thus determine the gravitational constant ''G''.'</ref><ref name=HarvLect>{{cite web|title=Cavendish Experiment, Harvard Lecture Demonstrations, Harvard Univ|url=http://sciencedemonstrations.fas.harvard.edu/icb/icb.do?keyword=k16940&pageid=icb.page80669&pageContentId=icb.pagecontent277503&state=maximize&view=view.do&viewParam_name=indepth.html#a_icb_pagecontent277503|postscript=<!--None-->|accessdate=2013-12-30|archive-date=2015-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712085157/http://sciencedemonstrations.fas.harvard.edu/icb/icb.do?keyword=k16940&pageid=icb.page80669&pageContentId=icb.pagecontent277503&state=maximize&view=view.do&viewParam_name=indepth.html#a_icb_pagecontent277503|dead-url=no}}.  '[the torsion balance was]...modified by Cavendish to measure ''G''.'</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Shectman|first=Jonathan|title=Groundbreaking Experiments, Inventions, and Discoveries of the 18th Century|year=2003|publisher=Greenwood|pages=xlvii|url=https://books.google.com/?id=SsbChdIiflsC&pg=PAxlvii|isbn=978-0-313-32015-6|postscript=<!--None-->|accessdate=2013-12-30}} 'Cavendish calculates the gravitational constant, which in turn gives him the mass of the earth...'</ref>

